Please ensure the following when working in this repository:

1. Write clean, well-documented Python code that includes type hints.
2. Follow PEP 8 style guidelines throughout the codebase.
3. Include robust error handling for all database operations.
4. Add descriptive comments wherever the logic becomes complex or non-obvious.
5. Use meaningful, self-explanatory variable and function names.
6. Structure code in a modular way to keep components cohesive and maintainable.
